column4: hi, can anyone help me with a failed 9.10>10.04 upgrade attempt?
i doubt it, lol. but i'm willing to try
worth a shot i suppose ;) upgrade manager crapped out with "An unresolvable problem occurred while calculating the upgrade:
there's a command line way to try and upgrade. not certain what it it is. i'll need to ask..
you see that? try on the command line --> do-release-upgrade
hello. you tried that command yet? just wondering if it's working yet
hi, yeah i tried it but i got the same message. looking at apt.log seems i have broken depends which im hastily trying to fix..
from apt.log - Package xserver-xorg-video-all has broken Depends on xserver-xorg-video-nouveau
what happens if you try --> apt-get install xserver-xorg-video-nouveau
not sure i understand... you mean it just reinstalls it? or you installing it right now so that it will be upgraded?
sorry, i didn't make myself clear. Ive just replaced xserver-xorg-video-all via synaptic
ahh, roger. well, that'll probably do the trick! i have to be going... good luck
me too, thanks for your help, ill get there!
